## Propagating Trace Context Through RabbitMQ Headers

The issue is that RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C trace context. You need to manually inject/extract it using `System.Diagnostics` APIs.

**Service A (Publisher) — Inject context into message headers:**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your publisher
private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Publisher");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (activity != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = activity.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"] = activity.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Service B (Consumer) — Extract context and link the trace:**

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Consumer");

// In your consumer callback:
void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    var parentContext = default(ActivityContext);

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
    }

    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent Process",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext);  // <-- links to producer's trace

    // Process the message...
}
```

**Key setup (both services):**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Publisher")   // or ServiceB.Consumer
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Why this works:** `ActivityContext.TryParse` reconstructs the parent span from the W3C `traceparent` header, so the consumer's activity becomes a child of the producer's — giving you one continuous trace across the queue boundary.

**Tip:** If you use [MassTransit](https://masstransit.io/) or the `RabbitMQ.Client.OpenTelemetry` package (available for newer client versions), this propagation is done automatically.
